sible loss of an important customer — became interested in the possibility of acquiring control the company was listed on the new york stock exchange but bernard d rubin acquired a list of shareholders and approached them in person in order to purchase their shares the rubins eventually achieved control and agreed that bernard would run the company as president mr rubin was able to steadily increase sales and restore profits changing the formula of the tootsie roll and increasing its size moving from manhattan to a much larger plant in hoboken new jersey and guiding the company successfully through the difficult war years when vital raw materials were in short supply when he died in  he had increased the sales volume twelvefold after his death his brother william b rubin became president and remained president until  in  williams daughter ellen rubin gordon took control and as of january  is chairman and ceo of the company for many years prior to his death her husband melvin gordon was chairman and ceo from  to  in  the company adopted its current name of tootsie roll industries inc the company has acquired several famous brands of confections such as the candy corporation of americas mason division  cellas confections  the charms company  warnerlamberts candy division  excluding gum and mints andes candies  and concord confections  facilitiesedit the companys headquarters are located on the south side of chicago in a portion of the former dodge chicago plant the company has a factory in mexico city where they produce tootsie pops and other candy products for the mexican market as well as for exports to the us and canadacitation needed there is also a candy factory in the area  neighborhood of cambridge massachusetts belonging to the subsidiary cambridge brands brands and productsedit tootsie roll brands and products include tootsie rolls and tootsie pops frooties fruit flavored chewy candy childs play assorted candies dots gumdrops and crows licorice candy andes chocolate mints charms blow pops and caramel apple pops sugar daddy and sugar babies caramels charleston chew candy bars junior mints cellas chocolatecovered cherries fluffy stuff cotton candy dubble bubble razzles and cry baby chewing gum niklnip juice confection wax lips flavored wax candy bonomos turkish taffy polar mint referencesedit  a b alison griswold  january  tootsie roll ceo dies at  we may never know how many licks slate magazine   a b kesling ben august   tootsies secret empire the wall street journal pp b–b   a b c andrew f smith  encyclopedia of junk food and fast food greenwood publishing group isbn   entry tootsie roll p   ellen rubin gordon  interview on abctv world news now reading  letter from clara tootsie hirshfield written when she was  years old  schlesinger hank  melvin gordon is dead at  led tootsie roll industries vending times retrieved    watt abigail  ceo and chairman of tootsie roll melvin gordon dies at  candy industry retrieved    strom stephanie  melvin j gordon who ran tootsie roll industries dies at  new york times retrieved    tootsie roll candies  cambridge brands cambridge ma  iconic factories on waymarkingcom  external linksedit tootsie roll industries web site tootsies secret empire a ceo in his s helms an attractive takeover target so whats next no one really knows wall street journal profile v t e confectionery products of tootsie roll industries andes chocolate mints caramel apple pops cellas charleston chew charms blow pops childs play crows cry baby dots dubble bubble fluffy stuff frooties wackowax lips junior mints niklnip razzles sugar daddy sugar babies tootsie rolls tootsie pops retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitletootsierollindustriesoldid categories confectionery companies of the united statestootsie roll industries brandsmanufacturing companies based in chicagoamerican companies established in food and drink companies established in  establishments in illinoiscompanies listed on the new york stock exchan